  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>chickpeas</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>wedges</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2527Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2527Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2527Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2527Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2527Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> along with the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>coriander</strong> (including the stems), a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Blitz until almost smooth then add the <strong>grated carrot</strong> and pulse for 3 secs further until all of the carrot is incorporated</p>",
